	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">WedNESday wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">With regards to my interrupt handling, is this correct? Or do the pins go down after the interrupt has been handled?</div>
<br />
<br />Not 100% but....
<br />
<br />I don't know about Reset -- but I'm pretty sure NMI/IRQ don't acknowledge themselves once they trip.  Pending IRQs can keep tripping repeatedy unless the software disables/acknowledge them.  The only thing that stops a dead lockup on IRQ is that the I flag is set.  If your IRQ code clears the I flag right away, the program will lock up.
<br />
<br />Likewise for NMI.  Although NMIs are automatically acknowledged by $2002.7 cycling.  Unlike IRQs, NMIs are edge sensitive... so an NMI will only trip once on the rising (or falling?) edge.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
